        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 15 at 5:23PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 523 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles east of Gastonia, or over Cramerton, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Gastonia, Uptown Charlotte, Huntersville, Central Charlotte,
Northeast Charlotte, Southwest Charlotte, East Charlotte, Northwest
Charlotte, Mt Holly, and Belmont.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
